# alpigolib

**alpigolib** is a modern, easy-to-use Python library that provides a collection of utilities for everyday development needs â€” from system and network inspection to cryptography, logging, and AI-related helpers.

It is designed to be **simple**, **modular**, and **production-ready**. You install it once and keep using it across all your projects.

> Think of alpigolib as a *developer-friendly toolbox* rather than a single-purpose library.

---

## âœ¨ Features

* ğŸ–¥ï¸ **System utilities** â€“ OS, version, battery, hardware-related info
* ğŸŒ **Network tools** â€“ connectivity checks, local/public IP, MAC address
* ğŸ§© **Utils** â€“ UUIDs, hashing, timestamps, slugify, random helpers
* ğŸ” **Crypto** â€“ hashing, encryption/decryption, secure key generation
* ğŸªµ **Logger** â€“ clean, colored console logging with optional file output
* ğŸ¤– **AI-ready architecture** â€“ designed to grow with AI integrations

